We had a good team composed of Julio Toro, Flor Meléndez, Carlos Morales, Raymond Dalmau, Armandito Torres.
In young people, I really like the work that Leo Arill does.
What is your greatest success in the Federation?
Having been part of the national team's most glorious time between 1988 and 1995, and the fact that in the early 1990s, the BSN had up to 17 teams in one season.
What have you left to do?
There are things I would have wished to put in place, such as the regionalization of minor categories.
